      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Pianist's Descent, Reprised</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tina Johnstone and Nancy F Regalado letter comments on Jan 18 article on murder of De Witt White; calls for gun control in New York City (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The New York City crime rate is down but illegal guns are still pouring into the city and young people are still shooting, still dying, as your article indicates.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The New York City crime rate is down but illegal guns are still pouring into the city and young people are still shooting, still dying, as your article indicates.</p>
        <p>Despite Mayor Giuliani's recent call for more jail time for juvenile offenders, the real outrage is the ready availability of unlicensed guns. As the anniversary of the Empire State shooting approaches on Feb. 23, the Mayor's priority should be to pursue those responsible for selling and distributing unlicensed handguns in New York City.</p>
        <p>TINA JOHNSTONE  Grymes Hill, Staten Island  NANCY F. REGALADO  Greenwich Village</p>
        <p>The writers are executive board members of New Yorkers Against Gun Violence.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
